records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody on WRIT.
Defendant waives his right to a preliminary hearing.  Defendant is bound over to Circuit Court Branch 3 for trial.
Information filed. Copy served on defense counsel.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the charge of Identity Theft - Financial Gain.  Convicted.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of fifty (50) months.  That is fourteen (14) months initial confinement followed by thirty-six (36) months extended supervision, consecutive to the prison sentence presently being served on 05 CF 97.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) No contact with Peter Hutterer;
2) Any contact with Holly Hutterer is at the agents discretion;
3) Maintain fulltime employment, work search or vocational training;
4) AODA assessment and follow through;
5) Pay restitution in an amount not to exceed $7,500.00 to Capitol One.  The State has 30 days to verify the exact amount;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) provide DNA sample;
9) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process.
The defendant has credit for 39 days.
Minutes.
